Executive Summary                                            December 20, 2007


A.     Accidental Release Prevention and Emergency Response Policies

     At the Ferro South Plainfield site, we are committed to operating and maintaining all of our processes in a safe and responsible manner.  We use a combination of release prevention programs and emergency response programs to help ensure the safety of our employees and the public as well as the protection of the environment.  This document provides a brief overview of the risk management activities that we have designed into and implemented including:

     A description of our facility and the use of substances regulated by the Environmental Protection Agency's Risk Management Program rule;

     A summary of results from our assessment of the potential offsite consequences from an accidental chemical release;

     An overview of our accidental release prevention programs;

     A five-year accident history for accidental releases of chemicals regulated by the Environmental Protection Agency's Risk Management Program rule;

     An overview of our emergency response program;

     An overview of planned activities to improve the prevention program at the facility;

     The certification that the Environmental Protection Agency's Risk Management Program rule requires us to provide; and

     The detailed information about our risk management program.


B.     The South Plainfield facility is a producer of precious metal products such as silver solder, pastes, and powders used in the electronics industry.  Formaldehyde solution is used at the facility in the precipitation of metallic silver from precious metal solutions.  These operations are conducted in small batch reactors.

